arbiter.Description: Enable arbiter mode. Possible values are 'disabled' for no arbiter, 'enable' to become an arbiter or 'host:port' to declare another host as an arbiter.  replicaset_master must be set for this option to work.

autoresync.Description: Automatically resync if slave data is stale

backup_copies_kept.Description: Number of backups to keep. Keeps one week's worth by default.

backup_directory.Description: Where can the backups be found.

bind_ip.Description: IP address that mongodb should listen for connections.

config_server_dbpath.Description: The path where the config server data files will be kept.

config_server_logpath.Description: The path where to send config server log data.

config_server_port.Description: Port number to use for the config-server

cpu.Description: Enables periodic logging of CPU utilization and I/O wait

dbpath.Description: The path where the data files will be kept.

diaglog.Description: Set oplogging level where n is 0=off (default), 1=W, 2=R, 3=both, 7=W+some reads

extra_config_options.Description: Extra options ( comma separated ) to be included ( at the end ) in the mongodb.conf file.

extra_daemon_options.Description: Extra options ( exactly as you would type them in the command line ) to be added via the command line to the mongodb daemon

key.Description: Key ID to import to the apt keyring to support use with arbitary source configuration from outside of Launchpad archives or PPA's.

logappend.Description: Append log entries to existing log file

logpath.Description: The path where to send log data.

logrotate-frequency.Description: How often should the logs be rotated. Use values from logrotate.

logrotate-rotate.Description: Number of log files to keep.

master.Description: Who is the master DB. If not "self", put the Master DB here as "host:port"

mms-interval.Description: Ping interval for Mongo monitoring server ( in number of seconds )

mms-name.Description: Server name for Mongo monitoring server

mms-token.Description: Accout token for Mongo monitoring server

mongos_logpath.Description: The path where to send log data from the mongo router.

mongos_port.Description: Port number to use for the mongo router

noscripting.Description: Turns off server-side scripting.  This will result in greatly limited functionality

notablescan.Description: Turns off table scans.  Any query that would do a table scan fails

nssize.Description: Specify .ns file size for new databases

objcheck.Description: Inspect all client data for validity on receipt (useful for developing drivers)

opIdMem.Description: Size limit for in-memory storage of op ids

oplogSize.Description: Custom size for replication operation log

replicaset_master.Description: Replica Set master (optional). Possible values are 'auto' for automatic detection based on install time or 'host:port' to connect to 'host' on 'port' and register as a member.

source.Description:
Optional configuration to support use of additional sources such as:
  - ppa:myteam/ppa
  - cloud:precise-proposed/icehouse
  - http://my.archive.com/ubuntu main
The last option should be used in conjunction with the key configuration option.

volume-dev-regexp.Description: Deprecated, use the storage subordinate. Block device for attached volumes as seen by the VM, will be "scanned" for an unused device when "volume-map" is valid for the unit.

volume-ephemeral-storage.Description:
Deprecated, use the storage subordinate. If false, a configure-error state will be raised if
   volume-map[$JUJU_UNIT_NAME] is not set (see "volume-map"
   below) - see "volume-map" below.
If true, service units won't try to use "volume-map" (and
   related variables) to mount and use external (EBS) volumes,
   thus storage lifetime will equal VM, thus ephemeral.
   YOU'VE BEEN WARNED.

volume-map.Description: Deprecated, use the storage subordinate. YAML map as e.g. "{ mongodb/0: vol-0000010, mongodb/1: vol-0000016 }". Service units will raise a "configure-error" condition if no volume-map value is set for it - it expects a human to set it properly to resolve it.

web_admin_ui.Description: Replica Set Admin UI (accessible via default_port + 1000)

charm-metadata.Name: mongodb
charm-metadata.Summary: An open-source document database, and the leading NoSQL database
charm-metadata.Description:
MongoDB is a high-performance, open source, schema-free document-
oriented  data store that's easy to deploy, manage and use. It's
network accessible, written in C++ and offers the following features:

- Collection oriented storage - easy storage of object-style data
- Full index support, including on inner objects
- Query profiling
- Replication and fail-over support
- Efficient storage of binary data including large
  objects (e.g. videos)
- Auto-sharding for cloud-level scalability (Q209)
  High performance, scalability, and reasonable depth of functionality
  are the goals for the project.
